-- Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Buenaventura, Candente, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-03T21:28:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/peru-stocks-atacocha-buenaventura-candente-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a third session, dropping
1.4 percent to 22,055.99. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell
1.3 percent to 2,888.63.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc
and silver mining company, fell 5.4 percent to 53 centimos after
zinc slumped for a third session in  London .  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
and silver producer, dropped 1.6 percent to 3.08 soles after
first-quarter net income declined 7 percent to $70.8 million,
said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, dropped 4 percent to $39.60 after
gold fell in  New York .  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, slid
2.4 percent to $4.10.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, declined 2.8
percent to 69 cents after copper fell in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
